		"notes": [
			{
				"category": "summary",
				"text": "Security update for Mozilla Thunderbird",
				"title": "Title of the patch"
			},
			{
				"category": "description",
				"text": "This update for Mozilla Thunderbird fixes the following issues:\n\nSecurity issues fixed in 52.5.0 ESR as advised in MFSA 2017-26 (boo#1068101):\n\n- CVE-2017-7828: Use-after-free of PressShell while restyling layout\n- CVE-2017-7830: Cross-origin URL information leak through Resource Timing API\n- CVE-2017-7826: Memory safety bugs fixed in Firefox 57 and Firefox ESR 52.5\n\nThe following bug fixes and improvements are included:\n\n- Better support for Charter/Spectrum IMAP\n- No longer mark other messages as read in search folders spanning multiple base folders\n- IMAP alerts have been corrected and now show the correct server name in case of connection problems\n- POP alerts have been corrected and now indicate connection problems in case the configured POP server cannot be found\n",
				"title": "Description of the patch"
			},
			{
				"category": "details",
				"text": "openSUSE-2017-1311",
				"title": "Patchnames"
			},
